text="Improvements to date handling">Improvements to date handling</fr:title><fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>11</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00CW</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p><fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00CW.xml"
addr="jms-00CW"
title="Forester 3.0">Forester 3.0</fr:link> improves support for journaling with date-specific trees. When a tree is dated <fr:code>YYYY-MM-DD</fr:code> and there exists a tree at address <fr:code>YYYY-MM-DD</fr:code>, the date field will be hyperlinked to the latter. This involves changes to both the executable and the XSL stylesheet of the <fr:link
type="external"
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-base-theme">base theme</fr:link>. The purpose of this change is to better facilitate daily notes / journaling.</fr:p><fr:p>Additionally, <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-005P.xml"
addr="jms-005P"
title="Forester">Forester</fr:link>’s data model now allows <fr:em>multiple</fr:em> dates to be assigned to a single tree simultaneously.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
