type="user">jms-00CY</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00CY.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Breaking changes">Breaking changes</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>11</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00CW</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p><fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00CW.xml"
addr="jms-00CW"
title="Forester 3.0">Forester 3.0</fr:link> introduces a number of breaking changes to the source language in order to facilitate maintainability, diagnostic support, and extensibility of both the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-005P.xml"
addr="jms-005P"
title="Forester">Forester</fr:link> tool and your individual <fr:link
type="local"
href="tfmt-000R.xml"
addr="tfmt-000R"
title="Forests and trees of evergreen notes">forests</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:tree
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>807</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00CZ</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00CZ.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Fall-through of undefined identifiers">Fall-through of undefined identifiers</fr:title><fr:taxon>Change</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>11</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00CY</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The fall-through for undefined identifiers in XML mode is removed in <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00CW.xml"
addr="jms-00CW"
title="Forester 3.0">Forester 3.0</fr:link>: previously when an identifier <fr:code><![CDATA[\foo]]></fr:code> was undefined, it was possible to write <fr:code><![CDATA[\foo[attr]{value}{body}]]></fr:code> and have this be rendered in XML to <fr:code><![CDATA[<foo attr="value">body</foo>]]></fr:code>.</fr:p><fr:p>This behavior has been removed, but you can nonetheless write <fr:code><![CDATA[\xml{foo}[attr]{value}{body}]]></fr:code> to achieve the same. For content that is being rendered by either LaTeX or KaTeX, simple fallthrough (naturally without attributes or arguments) is supported; therefore <fr:code><![CDATA[#{\alpha}]]></fr:code> will render to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>809</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00D0</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00D0.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Primitive formatting commands">Primitive formatting commands</fr:title><fr:taxon>Change</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>11</fr:month><fr:day>3</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00CY</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>As a consequence of the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00CZ.xml"
addr="jms-00CZ"
title="Fall-through of undefined identifiers">changed fallthrough behavior</fr:link>, several new primitives have been added to the source language, including <fr:code><![CDATA[\p]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\em]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\strong]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\ol]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\ul]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\li]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\blockquote]]></fr:code>, and <fr:code><![CDATA[\pre]]></fr:code>.</fr:p><fr:p>You can add further commands to your primitives using a combination of <fr:code><![CDATA[\def]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\iftex]]></fr:code>, and <fr:code><![CDATA[\xml]]></fr:code>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
